<TITLE> 755 colleges see 100% pass, 41 see 100% fail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 25 (bdnews24.com)Some 755 colleges throughout the country achieved a 100 percent pass rate in this year's Higher Secondary Certificate and equivalent exams, while 41 colleges registered 100 percent fail rates, the same figure as last year. Last year 674 colleges gained a 100 percent pass rate, while the figure for 2007 was 434, said education minister Nurul Islam Nahid at a press briefing following release of the results. The number of colleges failing to pass a single student in the exams has been gradually declining, from 298 in 2003 to 60 in 2007, said Nahid. "We don't want to see any student failing, so we are monitoring institutions with the worst pass rates and steps will be taken to assist them," said Nahid. b
